207
00:10:50,000 --> 00:10:51,433
Let me go!

208
00:10:55,767 --> 00:10:57,567
No. Wait, Manuel.

209
00:10:57,700 --> 00:10:58,567
Manuel, wait.

210
00:10:58,700 --> 00:10:59,833
- What?
- Manuel, wait.

211
00:10:59,967 --> 00:11:01,067
Don't, don't do this.

212
00:11:01,200 --> 00:11:02,333
No, give it.

213
00:11:02,467 --> 00:11:03,300
You can't...

214
00:11:03,433 --> 00:11:04,700
- Manuel, wait!
- What?

215
00:11:04,833 --> 00:11:06,067
Wait, here.

216
00:11:12,133 --> 00:11:13,300
Here's your phone.

217
00:11:15,767 --> 00:11:18,333
Don't leave...
don't leave, Manuel.

218
00:11:18,467 --> 00:11:19,467
Please.

219
00:11:22,400 --> 00:11:23,767
Here it is.

220
00:11:59,767 --> 00:12:02,800
<i> Manuel! Jeff! Jeff!</i>

221
00:12:02,933 --> 00:12:03,900
<i> Son!</i>

222
00:12:08,333 --> 00:12:09,400
Manuel!

223
00:12:20,300 --> 00:12:21,933
- Felma?
- Manuel?

224
00:12:27,933 --> 00:12:29,800
So I sound like Manuel now.

225
00:12:29,933 --> 00:12:32,333
Noah, I'm...
I'm sorry.

226
00:12:34,567 --> 00:12:35,667
How are you?

227
00:12:35,800 --> 00:12:38,967
Here, I miss Manuel...

228
00:12:40,133 --> 00:12:41,667
but I'm fighting it.

229
00:12:42,700 --> 00:12:43,933
I'm not contacting him.

230
00:12:45,033 --> 00:12:46,367
Hazel and I made an agreement.

231
00:12:47,500 --> 00:12:49,100
I won't break it.

232
00:12:52,233 --> 00:12:53,967
I was asking about your head.

233
00:12:55,733 --> 00:12:57,000
Not your heart.

234
00:12:58,300 --> 00:13:00,200
I know you still love Manuel.

235
00:13:01,867 --> 00:13:03,833
And that you only see me
as a friend.

236
00:13:06,533 --> 00:13:08,600
But, Felma, please,
don't rub it in.

237
00:13:10,000 --> 00:13:11,267
It still hurts.

238
00:13:12,433 --> 00:13:13,567
Noah.

239
00:13:14,367 --> 00:13:16,233
I'm sorry.

240
00:13:16,367 --> 00:13:17,633
What am I doing?

241
00:13:19,167 --> 00:13:20,467
I'm sorry.

242
00:13:20,600 --> 00:13:21,833
If...

243
00:13:23,033 --> 00:13:25,333
you're getting
weirded out by me...

244
00:13:25,467 --> 00:13:30,233
then maybe we should avoid
each other.

245
00:13:30,367 --> 00:13:35,333
I don't want you thinking
I'm using you.

246
00:13:35,467 --> 00:13:37,700
Just because I need
a friend right now.

247
00:13:37,833 --> 00:13:39,400
Oh, come on.

248
00:13:39,533 --> 00:13:40,967
You're being too serious.

249
00:13:43,567 --> 00:13:44,867
I can't turn my back on you.

250
00:13:46,200 --> 00:13:48,100
I'm not that kind of friend.

251
00:13:49,833 --> 00:13:50,767
Now...

252
00:13:52,400 --> 00:13:53,300
how's your head?

253
