Not your heart, okay?
Just making that clear.

254
00:13:58,000 --> 00:13:59,200
Ah...

255
00:14:00,833 --> 00:14:01,800
No more headache.

256
00:14:03,767 --> 00:14:08,200
Oh... No more attacks.

257
00:14:08,333 --> 00:14:09,433
But you know what?

258
00:14:10,167 --> 00:14:11,133
I'm still worried.

259
00:14:12,433 --> 00:14:15,800
Felma, why don't you reconsider
doctor's advice?

260
00:14:17,367 --> 00:14:19,700
Get a check-up,
so we know what's causing it.

261
00:14:20,500 --> 00:14:22,500
You know, At our age...

262
00:14:22,633 --> 00:14:25,733
we really need regular check-ups
to know

263
00:14:25,867 --> 00:14:27,467
if we're sick.

264
00:14:34,167 --> 00:14:36,133
Alice, it feels like
the tables have turned.

265
00:14:37,500 --> 00:14:39,333
Manuel keeps shutting me down.

266
00:14:40,767 --> 00:14:42,300
I feel like a loser.

267
00:14:43,533 --> 00:14:45,800
Well, that's how life is.

268
00:14:46,867 --> 00:14:49,467
As they say, the world is round.

269
00:14:50,833 --> 00:14:53,700
People who used to let us walk
all over them...

270
00:14:55,767 --> 00:14:57,500
change.

271
00:14:57,633 --> 00:14:59,200
They grow a backbone.

272
00:15:00,633 --> 00:15:01,633
Why?

273
00:15:02,633 --> 00:15:04,767
Didn't you use to step
on Manuel before?

274
00:15:05,733 --> 00:15:07,700
You want an honest advice?

275
00:15:07,833 --> 00:15:09,700
Accept the real talk.

276
00:15:10,600 --> 00:15:11,967
So? What do I do?

277
00:15:13,000 --> 00:15:14,900
You're sending Manuel
back to Canada, right?

278
00:15:15,833 --> 00:15:17,633
Focus on that.

279
00:15:17,767 --> 00:15:22,367
While waiting, bring back
your old strategy.

280
00:15:22,500 --> 00:15:23,867
Act nice.

281
00:15:24,667 --> 00:15:26,867
Give him what he wants for now.

282
00:15:29,133 --> 00:15:31,400
Let him see his kids.

283
00:15:32,300 --> 00:15:35,933
But, of course, stay vigilant.

284
00:15:36,100 --> 00:15:39,000
Set conditions for Manuel.

285
00:15:39,133 --> 00:15:43,300
The kids only, not Felma.

286
00:15:44,333 --> 00:15:45,800
You can't trust her.

287
00:15:47,300 --> 00:15:50,767
<i>Before Manuel leaves
the kids again,</i>

288
00:15:50,900 --> 00:15:53,867
<i>let them at least make memories
he can take with him.</i>

289
00:15:54,000 --> 00:15:55,800
<i> So don't interfere.</i>

290
00:15:55,933 --> 00:16:00,233
<i>After tonight,
he'll be yours again.</i>

291
00:16:00,367 --> 00:16:01,700
You're right.

292
00:16:01,833 --> 00:16:03,833
That woman can't be trusted.

293
00:16:05,233 --> 00:16:06,600
She's too cunning.

294
00:16:07,333 --> 00:16:09,267
She made me believe

295
00:16:09,433 --> 00:16:13,033
that that trip was the last time
they'd see Manuel.

296
00:16:13,167 --> 00:16:16,200
Turns out,
they were still meeting.

297
00:16:16,333 --> 00:16:19,267
That's why you should play
your cards well.

298
00:16:19,400 --> 00:16:21,700
Be nice while you're still not
in Canada.

299
00:16:22,933 --> 00:16:24,900
But be aware of Felma.

300
00:16:25,900 --> 00:16:27,900
She might be planning
something now

301
00:16:28,033 --> 00:16:31,633
that she and Manuel have already
got what they wanted.

302
00:16:36,033 --> 00:16:37,167
But...

303
00:16:38,600 --> 00:16:40,967
why is Dad looking
for a psychic?

304
00:16:42,367 --> 00:16:44,567
I also want to talk
to a psychic.

305
00:16:44,700 --> 00:16:46,733
So I can contact Jessica.

306
00:16:46,867 --> 00:16:49,000
Oh, that's perfect,
I know someone.

307
00:16:49,133 --> 00:16:50,700
- Sorry.
- No need, Didang.

308
00:16:50,833 --> 00:16:52,433
Joel already
recommended someone.

309
00:16:52,567 --> 00:16:55,367
Wow, Joel is amazing, huh?

310
00:16:55,500 --> 00:16:57,033
So many connections.

311
00:16:57,167 --> 00:16:58,500
Has answers to everything.

312
00:16:58,633 --> 00:17:00,000
All around.

313
00:17:01,767 --> 00:17:05,633
Mom, is it okay if we speak
with a psychic?

314
00:17:06,867 --> 00:17:08,567
I don't need a psychic.

315
00:17:08,700 --> 00:17:10,933
You're letting Didang fool you.

316
00:17:11,067 --> 00:17:12,467
No one's putting a curse on me.

317
00:17:21,100 --> 00:17:22,200
Me again?

318
00:17:23,200 --> 00:17:24,267
Why curses?

319
00:17:24,833 --> 00:17:26,700
- And why me?
- No, why her?

320
00:17:28,433 --> 00:17:30,033
Is she even listening?

321
00:17:30,167 --> 00:17:31,800
Aren't we talking about Dad?

322
00:17:33,200 --> 00:17:35,367
She's listening,
she can hear us.

323
00:18:05,467 --> 00:18:06,600
Mom?

324
00:18:12,800 --> 00:18:14,267
Mom, are you okay?

325
00:18:16,967 --> 00:18:18,833
Why are you asking that?

326
00:18:20,133 --> 00:18:28,800
Because we've noticed something
different about you.

327
00:18:29,900 --> 00:18:35,867
These past few days,
your mood has kept changing.

328
00:18:37,900 --> 00:18:41,233
You're becoming forgetful, too.

329
00:18:44,167 --> 00:18:48,133
And sometimes you just stare off
into space, Mom.

330
00:18:50,067 --> 00:18:52,033
There's really something off.

331
00:18:53,533 --> 00:18:55,800
Even with food.
it's like you don't...

332
00:18:57,167 --> 00:18:59,067
I'm not okay, Dear.

333
00:18:59,200 --> 00:19:01,533
I feel guilty because...

334
00:19:01,667 --> 00:19:04,000
because we're lying

335
00:19:04,133 --> 00:19:06,200
and hiding something
from Coleen.

336
00:19:07,567 --> 00:19:11,800
Maybe I'm still struggling
to accept that...

337
00:19:13,400 --> 00:19:15,933
Manuel is back with Hazel again.

338
00:19:20,400 --> 00:19:21,800
But don't worry.

339
00:19:23,300 --> 00:19:27,233
I managed before
when Manuel left me.

340
00:19:29,267 --> 00:19:30,767
I can handle it again.

341
00:19:31,667 --> 00:19:34,833
And I have all of you.

342
00:19:36,400 --> 00:19:38,833
You're where I draw my strength.

343
00:19:40,900 --> 00:19:42,667
Mom, the same goes for us.

344
00:19:45,233 --> 00:19:47,233
You're our strength too.

345
00:19:49,667 --> 00:19:51,567
We wouldn't be this strong

346
00:19:51,700 --> 00:19:53,833
if it weren't for you.

347
00:20:14,067 --> 00:20:15,267
Alice, what are you doing here?

348
00:20:16,333 --> 00:20:18,633
Hazel's not home,
she went back to the province.

349
00:20:18,767 --> 00:20:19,767
I know.

350
00:20:19,900 --> 00:20:22,367
She said there's an emergency
with Hilda.

351
00:20:22,500 --> 00:20:23,267
She had a miscarriage.

352
00:20:23,400 --> 00:20:24,900
That's why she sent me here.

353
00:20:26,400 --> 00:20:28,267
She sent you to watch me?

354
00:20:29,467 --> 00:20:30,933
She thinks I'm going to run
away?

355
00:20:32,033 --> 00:20:33,067
Manuel, no.

356
00:20:33,200 --> 00:20:36,467
Hazel just wants someone
with you while she's gone.

357
00:20:36,633 --> 00:20:38,633
I don't need anyone
looking after me.

358
00:20:39,133 --> 00:20:40,200
Chill.

359
00:20:40,333 --> 00:20:42,267
Can we not fight?

360
00:20:42,400 --> 00:20:44,167
Just give your wife this one.

361
00:20:44,300 --> 00:20:46,333
And I'm not here
to watch you, okay?

362
00:20:46,467 --> 00:20:48,267
I just want to sleep all day.

363
00:20:51,133 --> 00:20:52,800
Good day.

364
00:20:53,800 --> 00:20:55,400
Good day, Miss Precy.

365
00:20:56,667 --> 00:20:57,800
Manuel, who's that?

366
00:20:58,867 --> 00:21:02,367
She's the psychic that
Jeffrey's friend knows.

367
00:21:02,500 --> 00:21:04,800
Huh? What?

368
00:21:04,933 --> 00:21:06,667
You got a medium?

369
00:21:06,800 --> 00:21:08,533
Are you out of your mind?

370
00:21:08,700 --> 00:21:10,200
Alice, no.

371
00:21:10,333 --> 00:21:12,800
I'm just desperate
to try anything...

372
00:21:12,933 --> 00:21:16,267
to understand what Jessica is
telling me in my dreams.

373
00:21:25,300 --> 00:21:26,267
Yes, okay, friend.

374
00:21:26,400 --> 00:21:28,200
I'll call you later,
all right? All right.

375
00:21:29,433 --> 00:21:30,367
Manuel, wait.

376
00:21:31,367 --> 00:21:34,200
Hazel said not to let her in.

377
00:21:34,900 --> 00:21:36,933
She doesn't believe
in things like this.

378
00:21:37,067 --> 00:21:38,833
Well, I do.

379
00:21:42,033 --> 00:21:47,100
Sorry, but the house owner
doesn't allow it.

380
00:21:47,233 --> 00:21:49,233
You can go now.

381
00:21:55,300 --> 00:21:56,900
You know many things.

382
00:21:58,433 --> 00:22:00,867
Secrets that aren't yours.

383
00:22:02,333 --> 00:22:08,733
You're hiding something
and tolerating what's wrong.

384
00:22:10,367 --> 00:22:14,967
Because you're a loyal friend.

385
00:22:18,167 --> 00:22:19,900
Come in, Miss Precy.

386
00:22:23,700 --> 00:22:25,100
This way.

387
00:22:33,200 --> 00:22:34,300
- Jessica!
- Dear!

388
00:22:35,467 --> 00:22:37,933
I dreamed of Jessica, Mom.

389
00:22:38,067 --> 00:22:41,200
I got to apologize to her, Mom.

390
00:22:41,333 --> 00:22:43,467
And you were asking me
to forgive you.

391
00:22:43,600 --> 00:22:45,433
So tell me, what's the truth?

392
00:22:45,567 --> 00:22:47,100
What's the real truth?

393
00:22:47,233 --> 00:22:50,067
Dear, tell me,
what's the truth?

394
00:22:50,233 --> 00:22:52,967
Even just for
my grandchild's milk.

395
00:22:53,100 --> 00:22:54,333
I'll give you money.

396
00:22:54,467 --> 00:22:56,400
<i>Honestly, I don't even have to.</i>

397
00:22:56,533 --> 00:22:58,233
I already got what I wanted.

398
00:23:01,667 --> 00:23:03,100
Manuel.
